The paper proposes a novel convolutional neural network for false positive reduction in pulmonary nodule detection, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques (cs.CV). The network is designed with multiple scales and feature integration, which are common strategies in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of abstract information and end-to-end learning, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on a benchmark dataset and compares it with state-of-the-art methods, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR).
